Governor Perdue,   

I have recently learned that Superior Court Judge Leon Stanback is scheduled to retire September 1st, 2009.  Therefore, I am writing you in support of Judge Elaine Bushfan as the next Superior Court Judge for Durham County.   

Judge Bushfan was born and raised in Durham and has tirelessly worked to address and improve the quality of life in this community.  Since taking District Court office in 1995, she has been a tireless advocate of juveniles and the juvenile justice system as a whole.  Judge Bushfan recognized early on that the key to solving, or at least better managing, the growing criminal justice system rested with the youth of the community.  Judge Bushfan has publicly stated and worked towards creating programs designed to prevent youth from entering the judicial system.  Towards that end, Judge Bushfan worked with various Durham County officials and established the very first Juvenile Task Force in Durham County.  While this specific program has changed throughout the years the concept has remained, as has Judge Bushfan's steadfast involvement.  She also found her own "positive diversion program", known as the Restoration Institute for Leaders.  This program focuses on an array of judiciary, social, and vocational services as well as incentives for at-risk juveniles.  Thanks to Judge Bushfan's vision and efforts, countless juveniles from the Durham community have managed to escape "low academics, truancy, disruptive behaviors, and gang involvement." 

Judge Bushfan is perhaps one of the strongest advocates the citizens of Durham have in our continuing fight against crime.  Being a native Durhamite, Judge Bushfan knows this community and it's problems from a first-hand perspective.  A simple review of her service thus far clearly indicates that she also knows the needs and solutions to those problems as well.    

I would like to again respectfully request that you appoint Judge Elaine Bushfan as the next Superior Court Judge of Durham County. 

